# create map and display it
sanfran_map = folium.Map(location=[33, -100], zoom_start=4)

# display the map of San Francisco
sanfran_map
incidents = folium.map.FeatureGroup()

# loop through the 100 crimes and add each to the incidents feature group
for lat, lng, in zip(adop_df.LAT, adop_df.LNG):
    incidents.add_child(
        folium.features.CircleMarker(
            [lat, lng],
            radius=5, # define how big you want the circle markers to be
            color='red',
            fill=True,
            fill_color='blue',
            fill_opacity=0.6
            
        )
    )

# add incidents to map
sanfran_map.add_child(incidents)

# create map and display it
sanfran_map = folium.Map(location=[33, -100], zoom_start=4)

# display the map of San Francisco
sanfran_map
incidents = folium.map.FeatureGroup()

# loop through the 100 crimes and add each to the incidents feature group
for lat, lng, in zip(nadop_df.LAT, nadop_df.LNG):
    incidents.add_child(
        folium.features.CircleMarker(
            [lat, lng],
            radius=1, # define how big you want the circle markers to be
            color='yellow',
            fill=True,
            fill_color='blue',
            fill_opacity=0.1
        )
    )

# add incidents to map
sanfran_map.add_child(incidents)

Heatmap of the Areas which are Sancuso Adopted¶

In [111]:
from folium import plugins
from folium.plugins import HeatMap


map_hooray = folium.Map(location=[33, -100],
                    zoom_start = 3) 

# Ensure you're handing it floats
adop_df['Latitude'] = adop_df['LAT'].astype(float)
adop_df['Longitude'] = adop_df['LNG'].astype(float)



# List comprehension to make out list of lists
heat_data = [[row['Latitude'],row['Longitude']] for index, row in adop_df.iterrows()]

# Plot it on the map
HeatMap(heat_data).add_to(map_hooray)

# Display the map
map_hooray
